    "what_description": "Anisomeris brachyloba is a species of flowering plant in the family Rubiaceae, native to Mexico and Central America. The plant is an evergreen shrub that grows up to 3 meters in height, with branches that are covered in short, white hairs. Its leaves are elliptical in shape, measuring 4-12 centimeters in length and 2-5 centimeters in width, with a leathery texture and an entire margin. The inflorescence is a terminal, axillary cyme, bearing white, tubular flowers that are 5-6 millimeters in length, with four stamens and a single pistil. The fruit is a small, brown drupe that contains a single seed.",
