    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Anisomeris brachyloba are anti-inflammatory, where flavonoids and phenolic acids contribute to its analgesic and antipyretic effects by inhibiting the production of pro-inflammatory mediators. Antimicrobial properties of the plant have been attributed to the presence of saponins, which disrupt the cell membrane of microorganisms, thereby preventing the spread of infections and promoting wound healing. Anisomeris brachyloba also exhibits antioxidant activity, thanks to the presence of phenolic compounds that neutralize free radicals and protect against oxidative stress. Additionally, the plant's antihelmintic properties make it useful in the treatment of parasitic worm infections, with terpenoids and alkaloids being responsible for the anthelmintic activity. The anti-cancer properties of Anisomeris brachyloba have been linked to the presence of flavonoids, which induce apoptosis and inhibit the proliferation of cancer cells.",
