    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Anisomeris brachyloba are iridoid glycosides, which include anisoside A and anisoside B, as well as flavonoids such as kaempferol and quercetin, and phenolic acids like caffeic acid and ferulic acid. These constituents are responsible for the plant's anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties, which can be attributed to their ability to scavenge free radicals and inhibit the production of pro-inflammatory enzymes. The iridoid glycosides have also been shown to exhibit antimicrobial activity, which can be beneficial in the treatment of infections. The flavonoids and phenolic acids have been found to have anti-cancer properties, with kaempferol and quercetin inhibiting the growth of cancer cells and inducing apoptosis. Overall, the unique combination of these constituents in Anisomeris brachyloba makes it a valuable resource for the development of new medicines.",
