    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Anisomeris brachyloba are infusion, tincture, tea, decoction, and salve. Infusion and tea preparations are made from the leaves and flowers of Anisomeris brachyloba, used to treat fever and rheumatism due to its anti-inflammatory properties. Decoction preparation involves boiling the roots of Anisomeris brachyloba to treat skin conditions such as eczema and dermatitis, utilizing its antiseptic and astringent properties. Tincture preparation involves extracting the medicinal properties of Anisomeris brachyloba using a solvent, used to treat various health conditions including fever and rheumatism. A salve preparation is used topically to treat skin conditions such as eczema and dermatitis, utilizing the antiseptic and astringent properties of Anisomeris brachyloba.",
